.TH "gpiod_get_index_optional" 9 "gpiod_get_index_optional" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiod_get_index_optional \- obtain an optional GPIO from a multi-index GPIO function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gpio_desc *" gpiod_get_index_optional
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *con_id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int index "  ","
.BI "enum gpiod_flags flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
GPIO consumer, can be NULL for system-global GPIOs
.IP "con_id" 12
function within the GPIO consumer
.IP "index" 12
index of the GPIO to obtain in the consumer
.IP "flags" 12
optional GPIO initialization flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is equivalent to \fBgpiod_get_index\fP, except that when no GPIO with the
specified index was assigned to the requested function it will return NULL.
This is convenient for drivers that need to handle optional GPIOs.
